author: COMSOL
description: This example concerns two-phase flow in a porous medium which contains a low permeable lens. The heavier phase infiltrates the porous medium from above, and the low permeable lens is infiltrated only when a critical saturation at the outside of the lens is reached. As the saturation of the heavier phase is discontinuous at the boundary of the lens, this requires the use of the Porous Medium Discontinuity boundary condition.
label: low_permeable_lens.mph
name: root
